{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/gather-all-the-coronavirus-data-with-python-19aa22167dea", "time": 1683004734.44326, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/gather-all-the-coronavirus-data-with-python-19aa22167dea/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "A Simple Way to Gather all Coronavirus Related Data with Python | by Federico Riveroll | Towards Data Science", "h1": "A Simple Way to Gather all Coronavirus Related Data with Python", "description": "The Coronavirus propagation throughout the world is alarming. Up to today (July 15, 2020), there are over 13 million confirmed cases of Coronavirus. The objective of this article is to get the needed\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-simple-way-to-gather-all-coronavirus-related-data-with-r-b1e7ecb74346", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6", "anchor_text": "confirmed cases of Coronavirus", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/tree/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_daily_reports", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://www.openblender.io/#/dataset/explore/5e7a0d5d9516296cb86c6263/or/35", "anchor_text": "dataset", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://www.openblender.io/#/dataset/explore/5e2ef74e9516294390e810a9", "anchor_text": "Wall Street Journal", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://www.openblender.io/#/dataset/explore/5e1ded6b9516290a010e03ea", "anchor_text": "CNN News", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://www.openblender.io/#/dataset/explore/5d8852059516294231c596c0", "anchor_text": "ABC News", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://www.openblender.io/#/dataset/explore/5e32fd289516291e346c1726", "anchor_text": "USA Today Twitter", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://www.epochconverter.com/", "anchor_text": "unix timestamp", "paragraph_index": 9}], "all_paragraphs": ["*Note: I recently published the R version of this tutorial which you can find here.", "The Coronavirus propagation throughout the world is alarming. Up to today (July 15, 2020), there are over 13 million confirmed cases of Coronavirus.", "The objective of this article is to get the needed data for research and gain proactive visibility on COVID-19 by enabling the gathering of all relevant data into a Pandas dataframe.", "The CSSE is doing the amazing job of uploading the daily data here. However, it is wildly untidy and on many different datasets, so I sorted it and uploaded it as a single OpenBlender dataset:", "Let\u2019 pull the data into a Pandas dataframe by running this script:", "So now we have the -aggregated by day and by location- number of confirmed cases, deaths and recoveries.", "Here we can see the outburst of confirmed cases in Iran, Italy and Korea. We can also see Spain, France and Germany starting to rise.", "We\u2019ll gather COVID news and texts from these sources: Wall Street Journal, CNN News, ABC News, and USA Today Twitter (you can look for other sources)", "Every observation is the aggregation of news by day, we have the source which is the concatenation of all news into a string and the source_lst which is a list of the news of that interval.", "The timestamp (which is returned as unix timestamp) means the news happened in the interval from the prior timestamp to the current one (strictly before):", "Now let\u2019s get the mentions count for some countries of interest.", "Let\u2019s look at a word cloud from the last 20 days of news. *optional step (if you want to install wordcloud):", "Keywords in the early news such as \u201cmystery\u201d, \u201cinvestigating\u201d, \u201cdozens\u201d contrast with posterior keywords such as \u201cchina\u201d, \u201ccoronavirus\u201d, \u201cglobal\u201d. And even more with the most recent ones: \u201cNew coronavirus\u201d, \u201ccoronavirus epidemic\u201d, \u201coutbreak\u201d, \u201ccruise\u201d, \u201cnovel coronavirus\u201d etc..", "For this we can part from the Dow Jones Dataset and blend several others such as exchange rates (Yen, Euro, Pound), material prices (Crude Oil, Corn, Platinum, Tin), or stock (Coca Cola, Dow Jones).", "So now we have a single dataset with daily observations of prices blended by time. If we want to compare them, we better normalize them between 0 and 1, so that we can better appreciate the patterns:", "It\u2019s interesting how almost all of them (except for the Tin price) follow a similar pattern.", "Now, we will align the COVID-19 confirmed cases, the coronavirus news and the economical indicators data into one single dataset blended by time.", "To blend the data let\u2019s upload the datasets we created to OpenBlender:", "*NOTE: you\u2019ll want the \u2018id_dataset\u2019 for each dataset to use below.", "And now we just pull the initial COVID-19 dataset and we blend the new datasets we created by placing the \u201cid_dataset\u201ds from our created datasets on the \u2018id_blend\u2019 fields.", "Above we selected observations for \u2018Italy\u2019, aggregated by day in seconds (8640) and blended the new data.", "And now we have a dataset with the daily information of all the data blended by time!", "There is an enormous range of directions to go with this.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "An attempt to separate signal from noise. | MSDS"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F19aa22167dea&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fgather-all-the-coronavirus-data-with-python-19aa22167dea&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"u